               <scopecontent id="aspace_c2780d597235d5c3af8ac67e04d56c1c">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>Probably compiled by Agnes Harriet Elizabeth Grant (born circa 1835), the wife of Grant. The scrapbook includes paintings and drawings by several amateur artists, pressed plant leaves, and about seventy photographic prints. Images include portraits of the Grant family; views of Mont Saint-Michel in Normandy, France; and several photographs by an acquaintance, Sybil Williams, that show scenes in Scotland, October 1895.</p>
